some criticism i agree with your general ideas but there are a few scenes i disagree withor ratherwould have worded differentlyfor examplethe use of feelidentifypercievegender identity and genderits best not to use the words identify and feel because we dont identify or feel a genderthe only way you can feel male or female is the roles assignedhowever we can generally feel that our sex is wrongwhich is actually just dysphoriai think its best to not use the words gender or gender identity either  because they both refer to the social and cultural roles assigned to men and womengender identity being which role you identify with the most and how you express thatas trans peoplewe know that this is not the case for us but we have been lead to believe that gender and gender identity is when our outside doesnt match the insidehowever this description is inaccurate as gender has never referred to thisits always referred to the social aspectit would be much better to state that our sex does not match with who we are insidehence dysphoria rather than our genderas you statedthis has nothing to do with gender nonconformity and by using the term genderit just reinforces the idea that if you do not conform to your gender roleyou are trans
